&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role in a nutshell&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;You will be a lead resource on the global team at Luno which is responsible for all social media content distribution, community management, and reporting across multiple regions and on various platforms. Your chief responsibilities will be in curating content for Luno’s corporate brand on social channels, as well as engaging as Luno on social media so as to establish the brand as a trusted thought leader and employer of choice. Whether it be industry thinkpiece content, CEO amplification, engineering and product content, or employer branding, you will need to liaise with internal stakeholders to bring this content to life. You will report to the global head of social engagement, and be a part of the global social engagement team, stationed across many continents.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;In addition to this, you will be required to take charge of the team for approximately 4 months when the head of the department will be on maternity leave. This will mean managing the regional team leads of our general social media brand presence, nurturing strong relationships with local and global stakeholders, and being answerable for the success of Luno’s social media channels during this time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
